# Netlify SPA fallback. GitHub Pages ignores this file and keeps using
# `404.html` + the rafgraph/spa-github-pages decoder in `index.html`.
#
# Without this rule, refreshing any non-root path on Netlify falls through to
# `404.html`, which re-encodes the URL (`&` → `~and~`) and redirects. The new
# URL is still not a real file, so 404.html runs again, doubling the encoding
# every reload — the runaway `/?/&/~and~/~and~/...` pattern.
